A meta-analysis including 1,094 patients with curatively resected colorectal cancer treated with polysaccharide K, a main ingredient of 
 Coriolus versicolor, showed an OS risk ratio of 0.71 (95% CI: 0.55–0.90; 
 p = 0.006). The disease-free survival risk ratio was 0.72 (95% CI: 0.58–0.90; 
 p = 0.003) (
 Sakamoto et al., 2006).
